Title: Investigating Cue Placement and Selection in Tutorial Discourse Subject Area: Discourse, Text Generation Word Count:  
Abstract: Our goal is to identify the features that predict cue placement and selection in order to devise strategies for automatic text generation. Much previous work in this area has relied on intuitions, constructed examples, or unsystematic analyses of naturally occurring data. We describe a coding scheme for the exhaustive analysis of discourse, and report two results based on this analysis. 
